webpackJsonp([0xb4b702dfcde6],{5561:function(e,a){e.exports={data:{post:{html:'<p>Here\'s a question for my readers who are <a href="http://www.schockwellenreiter.de">Mac </a><a href="http://www.vfth.com/">Men</a> (or <a href="http://andrea.editthispage.com">Mac </a><a href="http://www.2020hindsight.org/">Women</a>): what percentage of actively used Macs run OSX? A fourth? A third? Half? I suspect my employer needs a OSX-capable machine to test our products, but I don\'t have any numbers to back up my suspicion. We\'re all Unix geeks who have no clue about Macs. Feel free to leave a comment.</p>\n<p><b>Update:</b> Thanks to Garret for the link, and welcome to a couple of new folks who left comments. I should also be a bit more specific. My employer sells server software for home banking and brokerage, so I\'m really interested in how many folks would use OSX for home banking with a web browser (either with a login/password or a key stored on diskette or chipcard).</p>',fields:{title:"How Many Macs Run OSX?",date:"18 Apr 2002",url:"https://papascott.de/2002-04-18-how-many-macs-run-osx/"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/2002-04-18-how-many-macs-run-osx/",prev:{fields:{title:"Rau Visits Nazi Massacre Site at Marzabotto",date:"17 Apr 2002",slug:"/2002-04-17-rau-visits-nazi-massacre-site-at-marzabotto/"}},next:{fields:{title:"Plane Hits Pirelli Building in Milan",date:"18 Apr 2002",slug:"/2002-04-18-plane-hits-pirelli-building-in-milan/"}}}}}});
